import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['month'], format='%m').dt.month_name().str.slice(stop=3)
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='month', y='temperature', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["temperature"].mean():.2f}')
    chart.set(xlabel='Month', ylabel='Temperature (Celsius)')
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pressure'] = pd.to_numeric(data['pressure'], errors='coerce')
    data['wind'] = pd.to_numeric(data['wind'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='pressure', y='wind', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between pressure and wind?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
